"Climbing Stairs" problem where you can take 1, 2, or 3 steps at a time.
For $n = 4$, the output is 7 because the possible combinations are:


The Formula: Tribonacci RecurrenceWhen you can move in steps of $\{1, 2, 3\}$,
the number of ways to reach $n$ is the sum of the ways to reach the three previous steps:
$$f(n) = f(n-1) + f(n-2) + f(n-3)$$

Base Cases:$f(0) = 1$ (One way to stay at the start: do nothing)$f(1) = 1$$f(2) = 2$$f(3) = 4$

